WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:53.970
Sea Charts and Fishmen

3
00:01:55.640 --> 00:01:59.430
Isn't this a treasure map?

4
00:02:00.350 --> 00:02:02.980
It seems to be pointing
to Cocoyashi Village...

5
00:02:03.390 --> 00:02:05.400
There's treasure in Cocoyashi Village?!

6
00:02:05.400 --> 00:02:06.730
Really?!

7
00:02:06.730 --> 00:02:10.360
That's my personal map...

8
00:02:10.360 --> 00:02:12.490
It's none of your damn business!

9
00:02:12.490 --> 00:02:13.780
Whoa there!

10
00:02:13.780 --> 00:02:16.450
What's wrong? You seem upset.

11
00:02:18.830 --> 00:02:21.330
What's this?!

12
00:02:21.910 --> 00:02:25.420
What in the world happened here?!

13
00:02:25.420 --> 00:02:27.960
It's the work of
Pirate Hunter Roronoa Zoro!

14
00:02:28.750 --> 00:02:31.380
So where were you, Hachi?!

15
00:02:31.760 --> 00:02:34.050
This wouldn't have happened
if you were here!

16
00:02:34.050 --> 00:02:37.890
Of course it wouldn't have!
If only I was here!

17
00:02:37.890 --> 00:02:40.180
This is unforgivable!

18
00:02:40.520 --> 00:02:44.140
Then you wouldn't know where
Zoro disappeared to, right?

19
00:02:46.150 --> 00:02:50.690
Well, all I saw was a
peculiar swordsman

20
00:02:50.690 --> 00:02:53.610
whom I'd never met before...

21
00:02:55.910 --> 00:02:57.410
It was him?!

22
00:02:59.870 --> 00:03:01.740
So you did see him, you idiot!

23
00:03:01.740 --> 00:03:03.410
Where did Zoro go?!

24
00:03:03.410 --> 00:03:08.880
He wanted to see Captain Arlong,
so I took him to Cocoyashi Village just now!

25
00:03:10.960 --> 00:03:14.510
That means there's no reason
to rush out and find him.

26
00:03:14.920 --> 00:03:18.260
He's looking for me, too.

27
00:03:18.260 --> 00:03:22.310
He said he was a guest
of yours, you see.

28
00:03:22.310 --> 00:03:27.100
And I didn't think you'd be
back so soon, Arlong...

29
00:03:27.100 --> 00:03:28.520
Zoro, huh?!

30
00:03:28.520 --> 00:03:31.480
That means I just need to
buy myself a little more time...

31
00:03:37.410 --> 00:03:39.530
Why are you getting in the way?!

32
00:03:39.530 --> 00:03:42.160
Everything's so close to working out!

33
00:03:45.660 --> 00:03:46.830
So close...!

34
00:03:57.680 --> 00:04:00.050
D-Damn it! You wanna fight?!

35
00:04:00.550 --> 00:04:01.800
You're being a nuisance!

36
00:04:02.510 --> 00:04:04.100
It's your own fault!

37
00:04:04.520 --> 00:04:06.930
This is what you get
for messing with Arlong!

38
00:04:07.810 --> 00:04:10.810
Nami! I'm so disappointed in you!

39
00:04:10.810 --> 00:04:14.690
Even after you stole
our ship and ran off,

40
00:04:14.690 --> 00:04:17.570
Luffy didn't suspect you for a second!

41
00:04:17.570 --> 00:04:19.820
He still trusts you completely!

42
00:04:19.820 --> 00:04:23.200
How could you just lie
to his face like that?!

43
00:04:23.200 --> 00:04:25.700
The only thing I trust is money.

44
00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:27.500
His naivete is his own fault!

45
00:04:27.500 --> 00:04:28.790
What was that?!

46
00:04:30.960 --> 00:04:34.210
It was all supposed to
go off without a hitch.

47
00:04:36.880 --> 00:04:41.840
Since you guys are so eager to kill
my eight years of hard work,

48
00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:43.350
I should be the one...

49
00:04:43.760 --> 00:04:46.350
who gets to kill you!

50
00:04:48.270 --> 00:04:52.440
You're acting more like a pirate
than before you left!

51
00:04:52.440 --> 00:04:53.730
Kill me?

52
00:04:55.570 --> 00:04:58.240
You, kill me?!
Don't make me laugh!

53
00:04:58.690 --> 00:04:59.860
You'd be wise...

54
00:05:00.660 --> 00:05:02.490
not to mock me.

55
00:05:04.620 --> 00:05:05.490
Oh, crap.

56
00:05:06.330 --> 00:05:08.870
If I stay here, I'm dead for sure!

57
00:05:08.870 --> 00:05:10.160
Lethal...

58
00:05:13.880 --> 00:05:15.630
Smoke Star!

59
00:05:16.750 --> 00:05:19.010
The bastard used a smoke bomb!

60
00:05:19.010 --> 00:05:20.840
Surround him! Don't let him get away!

61
00:05:22.340 --> 00:05:23.220
Now's my chance!

62
00:05:26.850 --> 00:05:29.350
I figured you'd pull
something like this.

63
00:05:29.850 --> 00:05:30.810
Nami!

64
00:05:31.560 --> 00:05:34.270
D-Don't...

65
00:05:41.150 --> 00:05:43.240
I have a job to finish.

66
00:05:48.580 --> 00:05:50.750
This was my only choice!

67
00:05:50.750 --> 00:05:52.870
N-Nami, why did you...?

68
00:05:55.460 --> 00:05:57.250
Now be a good boy and die.

69
00:06:03.800 --> 00:06:05.510
– Way to go, Nami!
– Way to get revenge!

70
00:06:05.510 --> 00:06:08.310
Now that's why you're an officer
of the Arlong Pirates!

71
00:06:09.390 --> 00:06:16.480
N-No way! B-Big Sis Nami…!
She k-killed Big Bro Usopp!

72
00:06:19.730 --> 00:06:21.280
That's what you wanted, right?

73
00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:22.950
To die at sea?

74
00:06:22.950 --> 00:06:25.660
Nami, I'm sorry for doubting you.

75
00:06:25.660 --> 00:06:27.910
You're one of us.

76
00:06:28.490 --> 00:06:29.410
One of you?

77
00:06:29.910 --> 00:06:31.830
I work alone!

78
00:06:34.120 --> 00:06:37.290
There's only one reason
I joined this crew!

79
00:06:38.250 --> 00:06:40.460
To buy Cocoyashi Village!

80
00:06:41.630 --> 00:06:43.090
Keep your end of the deal!

81
00:06:43.090 --> 00:06:45.470
I'll have the 100 million berries soon!

82
00:06:45.470 --> 00:06:46.470
Of course.

83
00:06:47.220 --> 00:06:51.430
I'd rather gut myself than
break a deal over money.

84
00:06:51.770 --> 00:06:54.140
That's the kind of fishman I am.

85
00:06:54.690 --> 00:06:56.520
Glad to hear it, Arlong.

86
00:06:56.520 --> 00:06:57.940
You know the deal.

87
00:07:00.230 --> 00:07:02.030
That girl gives me the creeps.

88
00:07:04.150 --> 00:07:07.030
She's really coming into her own!

89
00:07:08.910 --> 00:07:10.620
A witch...!

90
00:07:10.620 --> 00:07:13.750
She really is a witch!

91
00:07:17.830 --> 00:07:20.590
There it is! Arlong Park!

92
00:07:23.590 --> 00:07:25.880
Hey! Don't poop out on me now, cow!

93
00:07:26.260 --> 00:07:30.100
Yeah, Big Bro Sanji's kicks
must've really taken their toll!

94
00:07:30.430 --> 00:07:34.560
Hey! Not that way!
To the left! That building!

95
00:07:58.460 --> 00:08:00.080
It's almost like we're flying!

96
00:08:00.080 --> 00:08:01.090
Not "almost like"!

97
00:08:01.090 --> 00:08:02.590
We are flying, dumbass!

98
00:08:02.590 --> 00:08:05.840
W-We're falling!

99
00:08:17.520 --> 00:08:19.400
We landed!

100
00:08:21.690 --> 00:08:24.150
Hey! Zoro!

101
00:08:35.490 --> 00:08:37.370
We made it! We made it!

102
00:08:37.370 --> 00:08:40.880
Wh-What the hell...

103
00:08:41.420 --> 00:08:43.040
are you idiots doing?!

104
00:08:43.840 --> 00:08:47.420
What do you mean?
We're here to get Nami.

105
00:08:47.420 --> 00:08:49.430
You haven't found her yet?

106
00:08:49.930 --> 00:08:52.430
Oh yeah. Where are
Usopp and Johnny?

107
00:08:52.430 --> 00:08:53.680
Usopp!

108
00:08:54.310 --> 00:08:57.430
Th-That's right! There's no time
to be screwing around here!

109
00:08:58.180 --> 00:08:59.560
What's wrong?!

110
00:08:59.560 --> 00:09:01.770
That moron got caught by Arlong!

111
00:09:01.770 --> 00:09:03.810
We gotta hurry before they kill him!

112
00:09:03.810 --> 00:09:04.940
You're too late!

113
00:09:04.940 --> 00:09:06.030
What?!

114
00:09:08.240 --> 00:09:10.820
Big Bro Usopp is dead!

115
00:09:11.410 --> 00:09:13.570
He was murdered!

116
00:09:14.740 --> 00:09:16.740
By Big Sis Nami!

117
00:09:20.080 --> 00:09:25.000
West Coast,
Cocoyashi Village

118
00:09:20.710 --> 00:09:22.040
Hurry! Hurry!

119
00:09:22.040 --> 00:09:23.250
What's the big deal?!

120
00:09:23.250 --> 00:09:25.000
The Marines! The Marines are here!

121
00:09:25.420 --> 00:09:29.970
Some survivors from Gosa managed
to contact the government!

122
00:09:29.970 --> 00:09:33.680
The Marines are here to rescue us!

123
00:09:33.680 --> 00:09:34.430
See?

124
00:09:37.350 --> 00:09:39.230
We're saved!

125
00:09:39.230 --> 00:09:42.020
We can finally get off this island!

126
00:09:45.980 --> 00:09:49.240
So that's the infamous Arlong Park...

127
00:09:49.240 --> 00:09:53.320
Pirates settling down so brazenly
is surely a sign of the end times.

128
00:09:53.860 --> 00:09:55.320
Listen up, men!

129
00:09:55.320 --> 00:10:01.210
Our mission today is to liberate
the survivors of Gosa,

130
00:10:01.210 --> 00:10:04.040
the town destroyed
by the Arlong Pirates!

131
00:10:04.670 --> 00:10:06.340
But I can't help wondering...

132
00:10:07.170 --> 00:10:11.010
Would our brand of justice allow
us to overlook the castle...

133
00:10:11.470 --> 00:10:14.010
of this unchecked pirate?!

134
00:10:14.590 --> 00:10:15.890
– No, sir!
– No, sir!

135
00:10:16.300 --> 00:10:20.680
Our unit is to annihilate
Arlong and his men!

136
00:10:20.680 --> 00:10:22.690
Prepare for battle at once!

137
00:10:22.690 --> 00:10:23.440
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

138
00:10:23.940 --> 00:10:26.270
The 77th Marine Branch?

139
00:10:26.610 --> 00:10:28.360
Yeah. That's what it said.

140
00:10:28.360 --> 00:10:30.030
A new face.

141
00:10:30.030 --> 00:10:32.570
Someone go negotiate
with the one in charge.

142
00:10:32.570 --> 00:10:36.950
If two million isn't enough to keep
them from trying anything funny,

143
00:10:36.950 --> 00:10:38.240
get rid of them!

144
00:10:42.540 --> 00:10:43.910
It's a surprise attack!

145
00:10:43.910 --> 00:10:45.170
Captain Arlong! Look out!

146
00:10:55.220 --> 00:10:58.100
H-He crushed that cannonball!

147
00:10:58.100 --> 00:11:00.060
His bite is terrifying!

148
00:11:00.720 --> 00:11:02.560
Captain Arlong. The negotiations?

149
00:11:05.020 --> 00:11:05.850
Canceled.

150
00:11:06.770 --> 00:11:07.900
Alright! Let's go!

151
00:11:07.900 --> 00:11:08.810
Time to fight!

152
00:11:08.810 --> 00:11:11.530
It'll be a Marine bloodbath!

153
00:11:12.570 --> 00:11:14.360
Not so fast, guys.

154
00:11:16.700 --> 00:11:21.660
Officer Chew
(Kisser Fishman)
Arlong Pirates

155
00:11:17.030 --> 00:11:21.200
No need to send everyone
just to take out some trash.

156
00:11:22.080 --> 00:11:23.910
We'll handle it!

157
00:11:23.580 --> 00:11:28.540
Officer Kuroobi
(Ray Fishman)
Arlong Pirates

158
00:11:23.910 --> 00:11:28.540
Those humans must be idiots to
pick a fight with us in the water.

159
00:11:28.540 --> 00:11:32.420
Three of our officers?! This will make for one hell of a fight!

160
00:11:33.170 --> 00:11:36.130
That ship won't last three minutes!

161
00:11:38.300 --> 00:11:39.640
How peculiar...

162
00:11:40.100 --> 00:11:42.220
Commodore!
The cannonball was a dud!

163
00:11:42.220 --> 00:11:45.140
Fire another! We must
demonstrate our intent to fight!

164
00:11:45.140 --> 00:11:47.520
We're dealing with fishmen,
so stay vigilant!

165
00:11:47.520 --> 00:11:48.310
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

166
00:11:51.610 --> 00:11:53.440
He's been hit!
It's one of Arlong's men!

167
00:11:53.440 --> 00:11:54.820
Get him! Commence attack!

168
00:11:55.190 --> 00:11:56.280
Stop! Remain calm!

169
00:11:58.200 --> 00:12:00.240
You're one of Arlong's men, yes?

170
00:12:00.240 --> 00:12:04.160
I am Commodore Pudding Pudding
of the 77th Marine Branch.

171
00:12:04.160 --> 00:12:09.960
We're an elite Marine unit of some
renown! Perhaps you've heard of us?

172
00:12:09.960 --> 00:12:13.880
If you do not wish for death,
I suggest you dutifully surrend–

173
00:12:14.630 --> 00:12:15.380
– Commodore!
– Commodore!

174
00:12:15.760 --> 00:12:16.880
How dare you!

175
00:12:16.880 --> 00:12:18.090
Kill him!

176
00:12:19.550 --> 00:12:20.930
Wh-What was that impact?!

177
00:12:20.930 --> 00:12:22.850
No way...! Fishmen beneath the ship?!

178
00:12:26.640 --> 00:12:29.980
I'm sorry to bother you like this...

179
00:12:30.480 --> 00:12:33.690
but we've taken the liberty
of removing your ship's rudder.

180
00:12:33.690 --> 00:12:35.440
Wh-What?!

181
00:12:34.190 --> 00:12:35.440
Commodore!

182
00:12:35.440 --> 00:12:36.400
Are you all right?!

183
00:12:37.650 --> 00:12:41.120
Don't worry. I didn't hit
any vital organs.

184
00:12:42.620 --> 00:12:45.870
This is just hypothetical,
Commodore...

185
00:12:45.870 --> 00:12:50.290
but if one were to move a massive
rock directly into a strong current,

186
00:12:50.290 --> 00:12:52.130
what would happen to the ocean?

187
00:12:52.130 --> 00:12:53.090
What?!

188
00:12:57.460 --> 00:12:59.630
Rearranging the reef?!

189
00:12:59.630 --> 00:13:02.180
That's impossible!

190
00:13:02.590 --> 00:13:04.430
Alright! Right around there, Hachi!

191
00:13:04.430 --> 00:13:06.140
Gotcha!

192
00:13:06.140 --> 00:13:07.350
C-Commodore!

193
00:13:07.850 --> 00:13:09.480
A giant whirlpool just formed!

194
00:13:09.480 --> 00:13:10.810
The rudder's not working!

195
00:13:10.810 --> 00:13:11.690
What?!

196
00:13:11.690 --> 00:13:14.690
I told you. We removed the rudder.

197
00:13:15.230 --> 00:13:18.070
This rudderless ship is now headed...

198
00:13:19.530 --> 00:13:20.650
down to the sea floor.

199
00:13:38.760 --> 00:13:40.050
This can't be happening...

200
00:13:41.630 --> 00:13:43.760
This is reality.

201
00:13:44.800 --> 00:13:46.100
There's no way...

202
00:13:46.680 --> 00:13:49.270
we can escape from Arlong's grasp.

203
00:13:52.480 --> 00:13:54.230
Thanks for that.

204
00:13:54.230 --> 00:13:57.650
It was nothing. We know
everything about these waters,

205
00:13:57.650 --> 00:13:59.150
from the winds to the depths.

206
00:13:59.150 --> 00:14:00.360
It was a cinch.

207
00:14:00.360 --> 00:14:03.950
With our top-notch skills, no one
on this sea can challenge us!

208
00:14:03.950 --> 00:14:06.910
And let's not forget Nami's sea charts.

209
00:14:06.910 --> 00:14:09.500
Those are some damn
good charts, alright!

210
00:14:09.500 --> 00:14:16.090
Once Nami charts all of the world's
oceans, we'll be kings of the sea forever!

211
00:14:17.340 --> 00:14:22.720
Indeed, she's the key
to creating the Arlong Empire!

212
00:14:22.720 --> 00:14:23.760
It's a real shame!

213
00:14:23.760 --> 00:14:24.840
A shame?

214
00:14:24.840 --> 00:14:27.640
He made a deal to let Nami
and Cocoyashi Village go

215
00:14:27.640 --> 00:14:30.390
once she saves up 100 million berries.

216
00:14:30.390 --> 00:14:32.100
Are you serious, Captain Arlong?!

217
00:14:32.100 --> 00:14:34.440
You're really gonna let Nami go?!

218
00:14:34.440 --> 00:14:36.020
I have no choice.

219
00:14:36.020 --> 00:14:39.360
That's what we agreed to
eight years ago.

220
00:14:39.360 --> 00:14:45.910
When it comes to money, I'd rather
die than go back on my word.

221
00:14:46.660 --> 00:14:48.870
Say that again, and I'll kick your ass!

222
00:14:48.870 --> 00:14:51.620
Stop, Luffy. This has nothing
to do with Johnny.

223
00:14:51.620 --> 00:14:53.960
If you don't wanna
believe me, then don't!

224
00:14:53.960 --> 00:14:56.000
But I know what I saw!

225
00:14:56.000 --> 00:14:57.630
She killed Big Bro Usopp–

226
00:14:57.630 --> 00:14:58.630
Shut up!

227
00:14:59.000 --> 00:15:01.840
There's no way Nami would kill Usopp!

228
00:15:01.840 --> 00:15:03.590
She's one of us!

229
00:15:03.590 --> 00:15:05.680
But, I...!

230
00:15:07.010 --> 00:15:09.220
One of who now, Luffy?

231
00:15:09.640 --> 00:15:10.560
Nami!

232
00:15:10.970 --> 00:15:12.180
Why are you here?

233
00:15:12.640 --> 00:15:13.980
What do you mean?

234
00:15:13.980 --> 00:15:17.190
You're one of us!
We came to get you!

235
00:15:17.190 --> 00:15:18.650
You're such a pain.

236
00:15:18.650 --> 00:15:19.400
Nami?

237
00:15:19.820 --> 00:15:21.070
One of you?

238
00:15:21.070 --> 00:15:22.400
Don't make me laugh!

239
00:15:22.400 --> 00:15:24.860
You barely even function as a group.

240
00:15:25.860 --> 00:15:27.990
You witch! You've got some nerve!

241
00:15:27.990 --> 00:15:29.870
I saw it with my own eyes!

242
00:15:29.870 --> 00:15:31.120
How dare...!

243
00:15:31.120 --> 00:15:32.830
How dare you kill Big Bro Usopp!

244
00:15:32.830 --> 00:15:34.540
Big deal.

245
00:15:34.540 --> 00:15:36.790
Why not kill me and
take your revenge, then?

246
00:15:37.750 --> 00:15:38.960
What?!

247
00:15:38.960 --> 00:15:41.300
Let me give you a heads up.

248
00:15:41.300 --> 00:15:45.670
Right now, Arlong wants to kill
Roronoa Zoro and his men.

249
00:15:45.670 --> 00:15:48.180
Zoro just had to go
and do something stupid.

250
00:15:48.550 --> 00:15:51.560
No matter how monstrously
powerful you are,

251
00:15:51.560 --> 00:15:54.140
you're no match for real monsters.

252
00:15:56.850 --> 00:15:59.520
Hi, Nami! It's me!
Do you remember me?!

253
00:15:59.520 --> 00:16:01.360
Let's set sail together!

254
00:16:01.360 --> 00:16:04.650
Shut your mouth!
You're just complicating things!

255
00:16:04.650 --> 00:16:06.240
The hell?!

256
00:16:06.240 --> 00:16:08.610
Love is always a hurricane!

257
00:16:08.610 --> 00:16:10.490
Hey! Listen when someone's talking!

258
00:16:10.490 --> 00:16:11.490
Where's Usopp?

259
00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:13.450
At the bottom of the sea.

260
00:16:13.450 --> 00:16:15.290
Damn it! Cut the crap!

261
00:16:17.790 --> 00:16:21.340
So swordsmen don't mind
striking ladies, Roronoa Zoro?

262
00:16:21.340 --> 00:16:25.130
What?! You don't even know
what's going on here! Back off!

263
00:16:26.630 --> 00:16:29.840
I guess I'd be irritated too,
after getting my ass kicked.

264
00:16:31.390 --> 00:16:32.350
Hey!

265
00:16:32.350 --> 00:16:33.890
Watch that mouth of yours!

266
00:16:33.890 --> 00:16:37.140
Mind your damn business, asshole!

267
00:16:37.140 --> 00:16:41.060
Big Bros! This is no time
for you two to be going at it!

268
00:16:41.060 --> 00:16:42.730
That's right!

269
00:16:42.730 --> 00:16:45.280
If you're gonna fight,
can you do it off the island?!

270
00:16:45.280 --> 00:16:48.950
Don't butt any more
into our affairs, outsiders!

271
00:16:48.950 --> 00:16:50.610
You still don't get it, do you?

272
00:16:50.610 --> 00:16:55.370
The one and only reason I got
close to you was for the money!

273
00:16:55.370 --> 00:16:59.580
Now that you're broke,
I'm not interested whatsoever!

274
00:16:59.580 --> 00:17:01.040
You can have your ship back,

275
00:17:01.040 --> 00:17:04.420
so go find another navigator
to get you to the Grand Line!

276
00:17:04.420 --> 00:17:07.710
Go look for your
One Piece or whatever!

277
00:17:08.220 --> 00:17:10.300
Just get lost!
I'm sick of looking at you!

278
00:17:13.430 --> 00:17:14.810
Goodbye.

279
00:17:16.220 --> 00:17:17.470
Nami...

280
00:17:24.190 --> 00:17:25.270
Big Bro Luffy?!

281
00:17:25.730 --> 00:17:26.650
Nap time.

282
00:17:26.650 --> 00:17:27.400
Nap time?!

283
00:17:27.400 --> 00:17:29.740
At a time like this?!
In the middle of the road?!

284
00:17:29.740 --> 00:17:32.030
I'm not going anywhere...

285
00:17:32.610 --> 00:17:36.160
and I'm not interested in
what's happening on this island.

286
00:17:36.160 --> 00:17:37.870
I'm just a little sleepy.

287
00:17:38.200 --> 00:17:39.580
So I'm taking a nap.

288
00:17:38.750 --> 00:17:39.580
Huh?!

289
00:17:46.500 --> 00:17:47.460
Fine...

290
00:17:47.460 --> 00:17:49.670
Fine! Whatever! Die, for all I care!

291
00:17:49.670 --> 00:17:50.550
Na–

292
00:17:55.680 --> 00:17:57.680
Hey, Big Bro Zoro!

293
00:17:57.680 --> 00:18:00.060
What the heck are you thinking?!

294
00:18:00.060 --> 00:18:02.810
Arlong is out to kill us!

295
00:18:02.810 --> 00:18:04.560
Why aren't we running away?!

296
00:18:04.560 --> 00:18:06.820
Now that we know what
Nami's really like,

297
00:18:06.820 --> 00:18:09.740
there's no reason
to stay on this island!

298
00:18:12.950 --> 00:18:15.070
F-Fine!

299
00:18:15.070 --> 00:18:19.040
It was a short reunion,
but our role as guides ends here!

300
00:18:19.040 --> 00:18:22.870
I agree! I'm not trying
to get myself killed!

301
00:18:23.370 --> 00:18:24.370
Yeah.

302
00:18:24.370 --> 00:18:25.750
Take care.

303
00:18:25.750 --> 00:18:28.250
Well, until we meet again!

304
00:18:28.250 --> 00:18:30.010
Be well, you guys!

305
00:18:30.010 --> 00:18:31.420
You, too!

306
00:18:45.310 --> 00:18:46.520
Hey.

307
00:18:46.520 --> 00:18:47.110
Huh?

308
00:18:47.440 --> 00:18:51.070
Do you honestly believe
Nami killed Long Nose?

309
00:18:58.530 --> 00:18:59.830
Back there...

310
00:19:01.290 --> 00:19:03.500
I have a job to finish.

311
00:19:05.330 --> 00:19:06.960
This was my only choice!

312
00:19:08.710 --> 00:19:11.050
Back there...

313
00:19:11.380 --> 00:19:15.760
Nami stabbed her own hand
to make it look like she stabbed me!

314
00:19:18.300 --> 00:19:23.480
If it weren't for Nami,
Arlong would've killed me for sure!

315
00:19:24.310 --> 00:19:25.480
What should I do?!

316
00:19:25.480 --> 00:19:30.110
The Manly Usopp can't just
turn tail after being saved!

317
00:19:30.110 --> 00:19:33.570
For now, I gotta hurry and find Zoro!

318
00:19:34.780 --> 00:19:36.700
Wait... Is that him?!

319
00:19:36.700 --> 00:19:38.410
It is! Alright!

320
00:19:38.870 --> 00:19:41.950
Nami didn't kill him.
Is that what you're trying to say?

321
00:19:41.950 --> 00:19:43.160
Am I wrong?

322
00:19:43.910 --> 00:19:45.000
Who can say?

323
00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:50.170
I did tell her that she's just a little girl
who can't even watch one guy die.

324
00:19:50.170 --> 00:19:51.630
Maybe that made her mad.

325
00:19:51.630 --> 00:19:53.090
Whad'ya mean, "little girl"?!

326
00:19:53.550 --> 00:19:56.760
Does her chest look
like a little girl's to you?!

327
00:19:56.760 --> 00:19:57.880
Is that all you think–

328
00:20:02.350 --> 00:20:04.100
He's alive!

329
00:20:04.100 --> 00:20:08.560
No, I think he's dead now...

330
00:20:27.250 --> 00:20:29.040
You sure know how to trash a place.

331
00:20:29.620 --> 00:20:32.090
What's wrong, Nami?

332
00:20:32.090 --> 00:20:34.800
Nothing. I'm just here to rest a little.

333
00:20:36.090 --> 00:20:41.300
Breaking glass and furniture
just to rest is a bit much.

334
00:20:43.310 --> 00:20:47.270
If nothing's wrong, why are you
staring at that treasure map?

335
00:20:49.640 --> 00:20:52.900
We agreed that you can tell me
anything, remember?

336
00:20:53.320 --> 00:20:55.570
Something just made
me mad. That's all!

337
00:20:57.940 --> 00:20:59.780
Oh, them. Who are they anyway...?

338
00:21:00.410 --> 00:21:01.160
You met them?!

339
00:21:01.490 --> 00:21:04.660
Yeah. Captain Something-or-Other.

340
00:21:04.660 --> 00:21:06.580
He kinda seemed like a liar, though.

341
00:21:13.000 --> 00:21:14.840
I get it now...

342
00:21:16.000 --> 00:21:17.880
Yeah, that'd hit you hard.

343
00:21:18.300 --> 00:21:22.090
I'm surprised that someone
actually showed up to get her back.

344
00:21:22.640 --> 00:21:24.680
Friends, huh...?

345
00:21:26.850 --> 00:21:28.310
That word...

346
00:21:28.980 --> 00:21:30.190
for her...

347
00:21:32.270 --> 00:21:33.900
No word could be more painful...

348
00:21:34.820 --> 00:21:36.190
Usopp!

349
00:21:36.190 --> 00:21:38.440
Did Nami do this to you?!

350
00:21:38.440 --> 00:21:40.570
Sorry. That was me and this guy.

351
00:21:40.570 --> 00:21:42.320
You did it!

352
00:21:42.320 --> 00:21:45.200
L-Luffy! You're here?!

353
00:21:45.200 --> 00:21:46.450
Yeah. We just got here.

354
00:21:46.450 --> 00:21:48.540
Oh, I'm here, too! Nice to see you!

355
00:21:48.540 --> 00:21:50.580
Someday I'm gonna kill you!

356
00:21:50.580 --> 00:21:52.960
Oh! You're in pretty
good shape, after all!

357
00:21:52.960 --> 00:21:53.670
Shut up!

358
00:21:53.670 --> 00:21:57.050
Speaking of which,
we heard Nami killed you.

359
00:21:57.050 --> 00:21:57.670
Huh?!

360
00:21:57.670 --> 00:22:01.420
That damn Johnny!
I knew he was full of it!

361
00:22:01.420 --> 00:22:02.930
No...

362
00:22:02.930 --> 00:22:05.640
In a way, it wasn't a lie.

363
00:22:06.010 --> 00:22:07.720
It's actually the opposite!

364
00:22:07.720 --> 00:22:10.100
Nami saved my life!

365
00:22:10.640 --> 00:22:15.190
There must be some reason
she's in that fishman crew!

366
00:22:15.190 --> 00:22:16.190
No kidding.

367
00:22:16.190 --> 00:22:17.570
So, what do we do?

368
00:22:17.570 --> 00:22:18.980
Do we storm Arlong Park?

369
00:22:18.980 --> 00:22:23.490
H-Hold on! We gotta find out
what the story with Nami is first!

370
00:22:23.490 --> 00:22:25.660
Either way, it's a waste of time.

371
00:22:24.950 --> 00:22:25.660
Huh?

372
00:22:25.660 --> 00:22:29.580
No matter what you guys do,
you can't get rid of Arlong.

373
00:22:29.580 --> 00:22:30.500
Nojiko!

374
00:22:30.870 --> 00:22:31.870
Who's she?

375
00:22:31.870 --> 00:22:32.830
Nami's big sister.

376
00:22:32.830 --> 00:22:36.500
N-Nami's older sister?!
No wonder she's such a beauty!

377
00:22:36.500 --> 00:22:38.460
What do you mean "a waste of time"?

378
00:22:38.960 --> 00:22:42.340
Please, don't involve yourselves
any further with this village.

379
00:22:42.340 --> 00:22:44.130
Leave Nami alone.

380
00:22:44.470 --> 00:22:46.390
I'll explain what's going on.

381
00:22:46.390 --> 00:22:49.010
You'll want to leave
the island once you hear it.

382
00:22:49.010 --> 00:22:51.730
There's a Marine ship at the shore?!

383
00:22:51.730 --> 00:22:53.850
It's a ship from the 16th Branch!

384
00:22:53.850 --> 00:22:56.560
Maybe headquarters is taking action

385
00:22:56.560 --> 00:22:58.730
after what happened
to the 77th Branch!

386
00:23:02.150 --> 00:23:05.740
I am Captain Nezumi
of the 16th Marine Branch.

387
00:23:05.740 --> 00:23:08.370
Bring me Genzo, sheriff
of Cocoyashi Village!

388
00:23:09.120 --> 00:23:11.870
I'm Genzo, Captain.

389
00:23:11.870 --> 00:23:13.200
You, huh?

390
00:23:13.200 --> 00:23:15.750
Take me to the home
of the girl named Nami.

391
00:23:15.750 --> 00:23:19.540
Nami? But what in the world for?

392
00:23:21.090 --> 00:23:25.300
You simply need to lead the way.
